    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div rend="parallel">
                <p xml:id="KT375-kilavi">iravukkuṟikkaṇ ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi talaimakaṭkuc colluvāḷāy
                    irupoḻutu maṟuttu varaivu kaṭāyatu. </p>


                <p xml:lang="en">The confidante inquiring about marriage,
                    refusing also the [meeting at] night time, as if speaking to HER, while [he] is
                    behind the hedge during the night tryst. </p>
            </div>

            <div rend="parallel">
                <lg xml:id="KT375">
                    <l> amma vāḻi tōḻi yiṉṟavar</l>
                    <l> vārā rāyiṉō naṉṟē cāraṟ</l>
                    <l> ciṟutiṉai viḷainta viyaṉka ṇirumpuṉat</l>
                    <l> tiravari vāriṟ ṟoṇṭakac ciṟupaṟai</l>
                    <l> pāṉāḷ yāmattuṅ kaṟaṅkum</l>
                    <l> yāmaṅ kāvala raviyā māṟē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg xml:lang="en">
                    <l> Alas, oh friend, if he doesn't come</l>
                    <l> today? [that would be] good,</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> because the watchmen don't cease <note place="foot"> Cām. glosses <term xml:lang="ta"> tūṅkāmaiyiṉāl </term>, "because the watchmen don’t sleep", which is probably situationally, though not semantically correct. </note>  at midnight,</l>
                <l rend="indent2"> when even in the middle of the night</l>
                <l rend="indent2"> the small Toṇṭakam drums of those who harvest at night <note place="foot">Is <term xml:lang="ta"> pāṉāḷ yāmattum </term> a synonym compound of emphasis: "even at midnight itself"?  </note>
            </l>
            <l rend="indent9"> are sounding</l>
            <l rend="indent3"> in the vast  <note place="foot"> What is expressed by <term xml:lang="ta"> kaṇ </term> as an extension of <term xml:lang="ta"> viyal? </term> Simply an expansive field? Or does <term xml:lang="ta"> kaṇ </term> refer here to the sections of a field (cf. NA 400.2 <term xml:lang="ta"> nēr kaṇ ceṟuviṉ </term> )? 
            </note>     dark field, where the small millet become ripe,</l>
        <l rend="indent6"> on the slope.</l>


    </lg>
</div>
</body>
